column3:
Travis failed on all systems:

```
configure:21110: error: possibly undefined macro: AC_PACKAGE_NAME
      If this token and others are legitimate, please use m4_pattern_allow.
      See the Autoconf documentation.
autoreconf: /usr/bin/autoconf failed with exit status: 1
The command "test -n "$USE_SHELL" && eval '"$USE_SHELL" -c "./autogen.sh"' || ./autogen.sh" exited with 1.
```

I'd be
@laanwj If this is going to be changed I think it needs to be done another way. I'd rather find out if it is correct or not.\n

So `]VARIABLE[` is intentional syntax. I's unfortunate that searching for such symbols on google is hard, would love a documentation reference for that.\nBut it works so @luke-jr is likely right (and I don't see a need to correct something that is not broken).\n
